We need to prove that `map (λ _ => g) (RelIO.liftFinf n f)` equals `RelIO.liftFinf n (λ i => g (f i))`.

Let's expand `RelIO.liftFinf n f`:
`fin_range n |>.map (λ i => ⟨↑i.toNat, f i⟩) |>.toAssocList`

So `map (λ _ => g) (...)` would be:
`map (λ v => g v) (toAssocList (fin_range n |>.map (λ i => ⟨↑i.toNat, f i⟩)))`

And `RelIO.liftFinf n (λ i => g (f i))` is:
`fin_range n |>.map (λ i => ⟨↑i.toNat, g (f i)⟩) |>.toAssocList`

So we need to show that `map (λ v => g v) (toAssocList L)` equals `toAssocList (L.map (λ i => ⟨↑i.toNat, g (f i)⟩))`, where `L = fin_range n |>.map (λ i => ⟨↑i.toNat, f i⟩)`.

This is equivalent to showing that `map (λ v => g v) X` equals `Y` where `X` and `Y` are `toAssocList` of lists that are related by mapping.

We can try to prove this by showing that the lists themselves are the same after mapping.

