When we apply `AssocList.mapVal (λ _ => g)` to this, we're mapping `g` over the *values* of the `AssocList`. So, the key `↑(i.toNat)` remains the same, and the value `f i` is transformed to `g (f i)`.

The right-hand side `RelIO.liftFinf n (λ i => g (f i))` should be an `AssocList Nat β` where for each `i` in `fin_range n`, the pair `⟨↑(i.toNat), g (f i)⟩` is present.

