For the left side: `mapVal (fun x => g) (RelIO.liftFinf n f)`. The original `RelIO.liftFinf n f` at key `i` is `f i`. So, applying `mapVal` with `g` will transform this value to `g (f i)`.

For the right side: `RelIO.liftFinf n (fun i => g (f i))`. By definition, at key `i`, this `AssocList` will have the value `g (f i)`.

So, both sides should indeed have the same value at any key `i`.

